article.headline: IPFW 107, Anderson IND 59
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Zeljko Egeric scored 18 points without missing a shot and IPFW shot 63.3 percent (21-of-32) overall to beat Anderson 107-59 Thursday night. Egeric had a perfect game, going 5-of-5 from the floor, 4-of-4 from 3-point range and 4-of-4 from the line. He also grabbed nine rebounds to lead the Mastodons (5-11). DeWitt Scott also had 18 for IPFW. Demetrius Johnson scored 14 and Jaraun Burrows had 11 points and seven rebounds for the Mastodons, who led 50-27 at halftime. Rodney Holliday had 15 and Ryan Fultz 10 for Anderson (6-6), The Mastodons outrebounded the Ravens 39-18. Anderson shot just 40.4 percent (21-of-52) overall but went 70.6 percent (12-of-17) from the free-throw line.
